<article id=3D"content" role=3D"main">

<!-- #BeginEditable "Body" -->=20


<h1 class=3D"center">Mixed Fractions</h1>=20


<p class=3D"center"><i>(Also called "<b>Mixed Numbers</b>")</i></p>=20

<div class=3D"rtUp">
	<div class=3D"col">	<table style=3D"border: 0;">
		<tbody><tr>
			<td><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/images/fractions/pizza-1-1.sv=
g" alt=3D"pie full" height=3D"120" width=3D"120"><img src=3D"https://www.ma=
thsisfun.com/images/fractions/pizza-3-4.svg" alt=3D"3/4" height=3D"120" wid=
th=3D"120"></td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center;">1<span class=3D"intbl"><em>3</em><stron=
g>4</strong></span></td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center;"><i>(one and three-quarters)</i></td>
		</tr>
	</tbody></table> </div>
	<div class=3D"col" style=3D"width: 280px; text-align:center;"><p class=3D"=
larger">A <b>mixed fraction</b> is a whole number and a proper fraction com=
bined.<br>
<br>
Such as 1<span class=3D"intbl"><em>3</em><strong>4</strong></span></p></div=
>
</div>




=20



<h2>Examples</h2>=20

<div class=3D"simple">

	<table class=3D"center" style=3D"border-spacing: 10px;">
		<tbody><tr style=3D"text-align:center;">
			<td style=3D"width:120px;">2<span class=3D"intbl"><em>3</em><strong>8</s=
trong></span></td>
			<td style=3D"width:120px;">7<span class=3D"intbl"><em>1</em><strong>4</s=
trong></span></td>
			<td style=3D"width:120px;">1<span class=3D"intbl"><em>14</em><strong>15<=
/strong></span></td>
			<td style=3D"width:120px;">21<span class=3D"intbl"><em>4</em><strong>5</=
strong></span></td>
		</tr>
	</tbody></table>=20
</div>=20

<p>See how each example is made up of a whole number <b>and</b> a proper fr=
action together? That is why it is called a "mixed" fraction (or mixed numb=
er).</p>=20


<h2>Names</h2>=20

<p>We can give names to every part of a mixed fraction:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/numbers/images/f=
raction-mixed-parts.svg" alt=3D"mixed fraction 2 1/3" height=3D"104" width=
=3D"225"></p>=20


<h2>Three Types of Fractions</h2>=20

<p>There are three types of fraction:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/numbers/images/f=
raction-types.svg" alt=3D"Fraction Types" height=3D"113" width=3D"463"></p>=
=20


<h2>Mixed Fractions or Improper Fractions</h2>=20

<p>We can use either an improper fraction or a mixed fraction to show the s=
ame amount.</p>=20
<p>For example 1<span class=3D"intbl"><em>3</em><strong>4</strong></span> <=
em>=3D</em> <span class=3D"intbl"><em>7</em><strong>4</strong></span>, as s=
hown here:</p>

	<table style=3D"border: 0; margin:auto;">
		<tbody><tr style=3D"text-align:center;" class=3D"large">
			<td>1<span class=3D"intbl"><em>3</em><strong>4</strong></span></td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td><span class=3D"intbl"><em>7</em><strong>4</strong></span></td>
		</tr>
		<tr style=3D"text-align:center;">
			<td><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/images/fractions/pizza-1-1.sv=
g" alt=3D"pie full" height=3D"120" width=3D"120"><img src=3D"https://www.ma=
thsisfun.com/images/fractions/pizza-3-4.svg" alt=3D"pie 3/4" height=3D"120"=
 width=3D"120"></td>
			<td class=3D"huge">=3D</td>
			<td><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/images/fractions/pizza-4-4.sv=
g" alt=3D"pie 4/4" height=3D"120" width=3D"120"><img src=3D"https://www.mat=
hsisfun.com/images/fractions/pizza-3-4.svg" alt=3D"pie 3/4" height=3D"120" =
width=3D"120"></td>
		</tr>
	</tbody></table>=20
<p class=3D"floatRt"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/images/art/sage=
-looks-left.svg" alt=3D"dog looking" height=3D"212" width=3D"122"></p>=20


<h2>Converting Improper Fractions to Mixed Fractions</h2>=20

<p>To convert an improper fraction to a mixed fraction, follow these steps:=
</p>=20
<ul>=20
	<li>Divide the numerator by the denominator</li>=20
	<li>Write down the whole number answer</li>=20
	<li>Then write down any remainder above the denominator</li>

</ul>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<h3>Example: Convert <span class=3D"intbl"><em>11</em><strong>4</strong></=
span> to a mixed fraction.</h3>=20

	<p>Divide:</p>=20
	<div class=3D"so">11 =C3=B7 4 <em>=3D</em> 2 with a remainder of 3</div>

<p>Write down the 2 and then write down the remainder (3) above the denomin=
ator (4).</p>=20
<p>Answer:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center larger">2 <span class=3D"intbl"><em>3</em><strong>4</str=
ong></span></p>=20
</div>=20

<p>That example can be written like this:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/numbers/images/f=
raction-11-4-mixed.svg" alt=3D"Fraction 11/4 =3D 2 3/4" height=3D"110" widt=
h=3D"252"></p>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<h3>Example: Convert <span class=3D"intbl"><em>10</em><strong>3</strong></=
span> to a mixed fraction.</h3>=20

	<p class=3D"center"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/numbers/images/=
fraction-10-3-mixed.svg" alt=3D"Fraction 11/4 =3D 2 3/4" height=3D"110" wid=
th=3D"252"></p>=20
	<p>Answer:</p>=20
	<p class=3D"center larger">3 <span class=3D"intbl"><em>1</em><strong>3</st=
rong></span></p>=20
</div>=20

<p class=3D"floatRt"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/images/art/sage=
-looks.svg" alt=3D"dog looking" height=3D"212" width=3D"122"></p>=20


<h2>Converting Mixed Fractions to Improper Fractions</h2>=20

<p>To convert a mixed fraction to an improper fraction, follow these steps:=
</p>=20
<ul>=20
	<li>Multiply the whole number part by the fraction's denominator</li>=20
	<li>Add that to the numerator</li>=20
	<li>Then write the result on top of the denominator</li>

</ul>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<h3>Example: Convert 3<span class=3D"intbl"><em>2</em><strong>5</strong></=
span> to an improper fraction.</h3>=20

	<p>Multiply the whole number part by the denominator:</p>=20
	<div class=3D"so">3 =C3=97 5 <em>=3D</em> 15</div>

<p>Add that to the numerator:</p>=20
<div class=3D"so">15 + 2 <em>=3D</em> 17</div>

<p>Then write that result above the denominator:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center larger"><span class=3D"intbl"><em>17</em><strong>5</stro=
ng></span></p>=20
</div>=20

<p>We can do the numerator in one go:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/numbers/images/f=
raction-3-2-5-improper.svg" alt=3D"Fraction 2 2/5 =3D 17/5" height=3D"78" w=
idth=3D"332"></p>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<h3>Example: Convert 2<span class=3D"intbl"><em>1</em><strong>9</strong></=
span> to an improper fraction.</h3>=20

	<p class=3D"center"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/numbers/images/=
fraction-2-1-9-improper.svg" alt=3D"Fraction 2 1/9 =3D 19/9" height=3D"78" =
width=3D"332"></p>=20
</div>=20


<h2 id=3D"notwrong">Are Improper Fractions Bad ?</h2>=20

<p>NO, they aren't bad!</p>=20
<p>For mathematics they are actually <b>better</b> than mixed fractions. Be=
cause mixed fractions can be confusing when we write them in a formula: <i>=
<b>should the two parts be added or multiplied?</b></i></p>=20
<div class=3D"larger">Mixed Fraction:</div>
<div class=3D"two"> <span class=3D"lt">What is:</span><span class=3D"rt">1 =
+ 2<span class=3D"intbl"><em>1</em><strong>4</strong></span> &nbsp; ?</span=
><span class=3D"lt">it may be:</span><span class=3D"rt">1 + 2 <span class=
=3D"hilite">+</span> <span class=3D"intbl"><em>1</em><strong>4</strong></sp=
an> <em>=3D</em> <span class=3D"larger">3<span class=3D"intbl"><em>1</em><s=
trong>4</strong></span></span></span> <span class=3D"lt"><b>Or</b> it may b=
e:</span><span class=3D"rt">1 + 2 <span class=3D"hilite">=C3=97</span> <spa=
n class=3D"intbl"><em>1</em><strong>4</strong></span> <em>=3D</em> <span cl=
ass=3D"larger">1<span class=3D"intbl "><em>1</em><strong>2</strong></span><=
/span></span></div>


<br>


<div class=3D"larger">Improper Fraction:</div>
<div class=3D"two"> <span class=3D"lt">What is:</span><span class=3D"rt">1 =
+ <span class=3D"intbl"><em>9</em><strong>4</strong></span> &nbsp; ?</span>=
<span class=3D"lt">It is:</span><span class=3D"rt"><span class=3D"intbl"><e=
m>4</em><strong>4</strong></span> + <span class=3D"intbl"><em>9</em><strong=
>4</strong></span> <em>=3D</em> <span class=3D"larger"><span class=3D"intbl=
"><em>13</em><strong>4</strong></span></span> <img src=3D"https://www.maths=
isfun.com/images/style/yes.svg" alt=3D"yes" height=3D"30" width=3D"30"> </s=
pan></div>


<p>But, for <b>everyday use</b>, people understand mixed fractions better.<=
/p>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<p>Example: It is easier to say "I ate 2<span class=3D"intbl"><em>1</em><s=
trong>4</strong></span> sausages", than "I ate <span class=3D"intbl"><em>9<=
/em><strong>4</strong></span> sausages"</p>=20
	</div><br>

<div class=3D"def">=20
<p>We Recommend:</p>=20
<ul class=3D"disc">=20
	<li>For Mathematics: Improper Fractions</li>=20
	<li>For Everyday Use: Mixed Fractions</li>=20
</ul>=20
</div>
